   "source": [
    "# Example\n",
    "A simple demonstration of how `dfcosmic` can be used to remove cosmic rays.\n",
    "\n",
    "We will first make a sample clean image containing two fake elliptical galaxies and 10 stars. Then, we will make a fake cosmic ray mask with 10 cosmic rays and combine the clean image with the cosmic rays to make a dirty image. Finally, we will apply `dfcosmic` to remove the cosmic rays."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "47810b1e-d9a6-4705-afc1-19fb1065ca0c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from dfcosmic import lacosmic\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import cmcrameri.cm as cmc"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "c5df39e0-5db6-4233-a0cf-dcc57a3f25a6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def make_2d_rotated_gaussian(shape, amplitude, x0, y0, sigma_x, sigma_y, theta):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Create a 2D elliptical Gaussian with rotation\"\"\"\n",
    "    y, x = np.ogrid[:shape[0], :shape[1]]\n",
    "    x = x - x0\n",
    "    y = y - y0\n",
    "\n",
    "    x_rot = x * np.cos(theta) + y * np.sin(theta)\n",
    "    y_rot = -x * np.sin(theta) + y * np.cos(theta)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return amplitude * np.exp(\n",
    "        -(x_rot ** 2 / (2 * sigma_x ** 2) +\n",
    "          y_rot ** 2 / (2 * sigma_y ** 2))\n",
    "    )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "1ab09b7a-759c-4127-a62c-01351438ea4b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "shape = (100, 100)\n",
    "\n",
    "point_sources = [\n",
    "    (1.0, 20, 20, 2.0, 2.0, np.radians(30)),    # Bottom left\n",
    "    (1.6, 80, 80, 2.0, 2.0, np.radians(60)),    # Top right\n",
    "    (0.9, 30, 70, 2.0, 2.0, np.radians(45)),    # Top left\n",
    "    (0.7, 70, 30, 2.0, 2.0, np.radians(120)),   # Bottom right\n",
    "    (0.85, 50, 50, 2.0, 2.0, np.radians(0)),    # Center\n",
    "    (1.5, 20, 80, 2.0, 2.0, np.radians(90)),   # Top left corner\n",
    "    (0.75, 80, 20, 2.0, 2.0, np.radians(150)),  # Bottom right corner\n",
    "    (2.0, 65, 55, 2.0, 2.0, np.radians(75)),    # Near center\n",
    "    (0.9, 70, 60, 2.0, 2.0, np.radians(15)),    # Near center\n",
    "    (0.85, 35, 45, 2.0, 2.0, np.radians(135))   # Near center\n",
    "]\n",
    "# Extended \"galaxy\" sources (much larger sigma values and higher ellipticity)\n",
    "galaxy_sources = [\n",
    "    # Edge-on galaxy\n",
    "    (0.5, 40, 75, 12.0, 3.0, np.radians(135)),  # More elongated\n",
    "    # Face-on spiral galaxy (more circular)\n",
    "    (0.4, 75, 35, 8.0, 7.0, np.radians(30))\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Combine all sources\n",
    "sources = point_sources + galaxy_sources\n",
    "# Create combined image\n",
    "image_clean = np.zeros(shape)\n",
    "noise_level = 2e-2  # Adjust this value to control noise amount\n",
    "noise =  np.random.normal(noise_level, noise_level, image_clean.shape)\n",
    "image_clean += noise\n",
    "for amp, x0, y0, sx, sy, theta in sources:\n",
    "    image_clean += make_2d_rotated_gaussian(shape, amp, x0, y0, sx, sy, theta)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "1dab9419-ca17-4565-b6f4-24c3f353b1c0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x600 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Display the image\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))\n",
    "plt.imshow(image_clean, origin='lower', cmap=cmc.lipari)\n",
    "plt.colorbar(label='Flux', shrink=0.8)\n",
    "plt.title('Clean Mock Image')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('X pixel')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Y pixel')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "6c56812a-8814-4ecb-9e05-442586e36488",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create cosmic ray mask\n",
    "cosmicray_xpos = np.random.randint(0, 100, 10)\n",
    "cosmicray_ypos = np.random.randint(0, 100, 10)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "crmask_real = np.zeros(shape)\n",
    "crmask_real[cosmicray_xpos, cosmicray_ypos] = 1.0"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "1aa4d080-9531-48f1-9b47-4dd953dd60a9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Display the image\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))\n",
    "plt.imshow(crmask_real, origin='lower', cmap=cmc.lajolla)\n",
    "plt.title('Cosmic Ray Mask')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('X pixel')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Y pixel')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "0fbd1572-a784-4ca3-a6fc-ba7ab28096fc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x600 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Generate random values for each pixel\n",
    "random_intensities = np.random.uniform(1, 100, crmask_real.shape)\n",
    "# Apply only where cosmic rays exist\n",
    "image_dirty = image_clean + random_intensities * crmask_real\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display the image\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))\n",
    "plt.imshow(image_dirty, origin='lower', cmap=cmc.lipari, vmin=0, vmax=2)\n",
    "plt.colorbar(label='Flux', shrink=0.8)\n",
    "plt.title('Dirty Mock Image')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('X pixel')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Y pixel')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "6c0c3787-e8ef-49f0-af06-c50865e505c1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "image_dfcosmic, crmask_dfcosmic = lacosmic(\n",
    "    image = image_dirty.astype(np.float32), \n",
    "    objlim = 4,\n",
    "    sigfrac = 0.5,\n",
    "    sigclip = 4.5,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },

    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(ncols=5, nrows=1, figsize=(16, 4))\n",
